<br>
2.) Board participation is HIGHLY suggested; in-game socialization is only Half of the guild experience. Visit the boards, at least once a week...  Much more often if your an officer.<br>
<br>
3.) Cursing/Spamming guildchat is not allowed.  Tho' we are more of a laid-back guild and Do have fun in guildchat we need to keep it semi-respectable.  Treat your fellow guildmates with the respect you'd want to be treated with.<br>
<br>
4.)Tho' we do like to help each other here to the mutual benefit of all that does not entitle you to expect your guildies to drop whatever They are doing to come Res/PL/chase off evils... Make your request(s) either here or in-game (Both places would be best) and if people can help they will...<br>
<br>
5.) PK policy - WoR isnt a PK guild, tho we DO have those that PK in it. As such you are not Required to engage the enemy whenever you see him/her in zone. Play how you want to play. However we DO encourage you to adopt a LnS (loot an Scoot) policy and discourage Corpse Camping unless the offender is a known CC'er themselves...<br>
<br>
6.) Xteaming is not allowed.  No need to assist evil or newty teams, they have their own numbers...<br>
<br>
7.) Cursing/Spamming/Behaving like an Idiot in /ooc if frowned upon...  Use your head and remember while you wear the WoR tag what you Do/Say reflects on the Entire guild... Think Before you Speak.<br>
<br>
8.) Raid Policy - WoR is not a Raid Guild, tho we Do do some Raids and of course would like to see you there, you are not Required to do so.<br>
<br>
9.) Same Team Training will NOT be tolerated under ANY circumstances and will be dealt with severely and quickly...<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
